[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":791},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fcss\u002F2020\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fcss-design-patterns-oocss\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fcss\u002F2020\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fcss-design-patterns-oocss\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fcss\u002F2020\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fcss-design-patterns-oocss\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fcss\u002F2020\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fcss-design-patterns-oocss\u002F":767,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fcss\u002F2020\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fcss-design-patterns-oocss\u002F":776},"\u002Fcss\u002F20200517\u002F168089779\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":751,"date":752,"description":753,"extension":754,"lang":755,"meta":756,"navigation":330,"path":757,"readingMinutes":758,"seo":759,"standalone":760,"stem":761,"tags":762,"tldr":764,"updated":752,"url":765,"__hash__":766},"content\u002Fen\u002FCSS\u002Fcss-design-patterns-oocss.md","CSS Design Patterns — OOCSS","2227418287",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":744},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,37,40,43,85,88,91,94,263,286,392,398,418,421,424,427,430,493,496,570,588,601,722,725,729,740],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"OOCSS is another CSS design pattern. The biggest framework using it is Bootstrap.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"oocss","OOCSS",[17,25,26],{},"OOCSS stands for \"Object Oriented CSS\". The two core principles:",[28,29,30,34],"ul",{},[31,32,33],"li",{},"Separation of content from container",[31,35,36],{},"Separation of structure from skin",[17,38,39],{},"These two ideas massively improve CSS extensibility and flexibility. If you've used Bootstrap, you've already been doing OOCSS without realising — Bootstrap is built on OOCSS, where each class can stand on its own.",[17,41,42],{},"Example — you don't need to know CSS, just read the docs, and you can apply Bootstrap styles:",[44,45,50],"pre",{"className":46,"code":47,"language":48,"meta":49,"style":49},"language-html shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\u003Ch1 class=\"text-left text-danger d-flex\">This is an h1\u003C\u002Fh1>\n","html","",[51,52,53],"code",{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,55,58,62,66,70,73,77,80,82],"span",{"class":56,"line":57},"line",1,[54,59,61],{"class":60},"sMAXC","\u003C",[54,63,65],{"class":64},"sKpQp","h1",[54,67,69],{"class":68},"sCcAr"," class",[54,71,72],{"class":60},"=",[54,74,76],{"class":75},"sTRMh","\"text-left text-danger d-flex\"",[54,78,79],{"class":60},">This is an h1\u003C\u002F",[54,81,65],{"class":64},[54,83,84],{"class":60},">\n",[17,86,87],{},"In OOCSS, each class is a self-contained CSS unit. This is similar to SMACSS's Module concept.",[12,89,33],{"id":90},"separation-of-content-from-container",[17,92,93],{},"The key idea — don't get locked into a specific layout. What does that look like?",[44,95,99],{"className":96,"code":97,"language":98,"meta":49,"style":49},"language-scss shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast",".header {\n  color: yellow;\n  width: 50px;\n  height: 50px;\n}\n.content {\n  color: red;\n  width: 50px;\n  height: 50px;\n}\n.footer {\n  color: blue;\n  width: 50px;\n  height: 50px;\n}\n","scss",[51,100,101,109,124,141,155,161,169,181,194,207,212,220,232,245,258],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,102,103,106],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,104,105],{"class":68},".header",[54,107,108],{"class":60}," {\n",[54,110,112,115,118,121],{"class":56,"line":111},2,[54,113,114],{"class":68},"  color",[54,116,117],{"class":60},": ",[54,119,120],{"class":68},"yellow",[54,122,123],{"class":60},";\n",[54,125,127,130,132,135,139],{"class":56,"line":126},3,[54,128,129],{"class":68},"  width",[54,131,117],{"class":60},[54,133,134],{"class":68},"50",[54,136,138],{"class":137},"sWyjQ","px",[54,140,123],{"class":60},[54,142,144,147,149,151,153],{"class":56,"line":143},4,[54,145,146],{"class":68},"  height",[54,148,117],{"class":60},[54,150,134],{"class":68},[54,152,138],{"class":137},[54,154,123],{"class":60},[54,156,158],{"class":56,"line":157},5,[54,159,160],{"class":60},"}\n",[54,162,164,167],{"class":56,"line":163},6,[54,165,166],{"class":68},".content",[54,168,108],{"class":60},[54,170,172,174,176,179],{"class":56,"line":171},7,[54,173,114],{"class":68},[54,175,117],{"class":60},[54,177,178],{"class":68},"red",[54,180,123],{"class":60},[54,182,184,186,188,190,192],{"class":56,"line":183},8,[54,185,129],{"class":68},[54,187,117],{"class":60},[54,189,134],{"class":68},[54,191,138],{"class":137},[54,193,123],{"class":60},[54,195,197,199,201,203,205],{"class":56,"line":196},9,[54,198,146],{"class":68},[54,200,117],{"class":60},[54,202,134],{"class":68},[54,204,138],{"class":137},[54,206,123],{"class":60},[54,208,210],{"class":56,"line":209},10,[54,211,160],{"class":60},[54,213,215,218],{"class":56,"line":214},11,[54,216,217],{"class":68},".footer",[54,219,108],{"class":60},[54,221,223,225,227,230],{"class":56,"line":222},12,[54,224,114],{"class":68},[54,226,117],{"class":60},[54,228,229],{"class":68},"blue",[54,231,123],{"class":60},[54,233,235,237,239,241,243],{"class":56,"line":234},13,[54,236,129],{"class":68},[54,238,117],{"class":60},[54,240,134],{"class":68},[54,242,138],{"class":137},[54,244,123],{"class":60},[54,246,248,250,252,254,256],{"class":56,"line":247},14,[54,249,146],{"class":68},[54,251,117],{"class":60},[54,253,134],{"class":68},[54,255,138],{"class":137},[54,257,123],{"class":60},[54,259,261],{"class":56,"line":260},15,[54,262,160],{"class":60},[17,264,265,267,268,267,270,272,273,276,277,280,281,276,283,285],{},[51,266,105],{},", ",[51,269,166],{},[51,271,217],{}," all share the same ",[51,274,275],{},"width"," and ",[51,278,279],{},"height",". If you use this pattern in 100 places, you're writing ",[51,282,275],{},[51,284,279],{}," 100 times — and changing the width means updating 100 places. The fix:",[44,287,289],{"className":96,"code":288,"language":98,"meta":49,"style":49},".container {\n  width: 50px;\n  height: 50px;\n}\n\n.header {\n  color: yellow;\n}\n.content {\n  color: red;\n}\n.footer {\n  color: blue;\n}\n",[51,290,291,298,310,322,326,332,338,348,352,358,368,372,378,388],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,292,293,296],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,294,295],{"class":68},".container",[54,297,108],{"class":60},[54,299,300,302,304,306,308],{"class":56,"line":111},[54,301,129],{"class":68},[54,303,117],{"class":60},[54,305,134],{"class":68},[54,307,138],{"class":137},[54,309,123],{"class":60},[54,311,312,314,316,318,320],{"class":56,"line":126},[54,313,146],{"class":68},[54,315,117],{"class":60},[54,317,134],{"class":68},[54,319,138],{"class":137},[54,321,123],{"class":60},[54,323,324],{"class":56,"line":143},[54,325,160],{"class":60},[54,327,328],{"class":56,"line":157},[54,329,331],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":330},true,"\n",[54,333,334,336],{"class":56,"line":163},[54,335,105],{"class":68},[54,337,108],{"class":60},[54,339,340,342,344,346],{"class":56,"line":171},[54,341,114],{"class":68},[54,343,117],{"class":60},[54,345,120],{"class":68},[54,347,123],{"class":60},[54,349,350],{"class":56,"line":183},[54,351,160],{"class":60},[54,353,354,356],{"class":56,"line":196},[54,355,166],{"class":68},[54,357,108],{"class":60},[54,359,360,362,364,366],{"class":56,"line":209},[54,361,114],{"class":68},[54,363,117],{"class":60},[54,365,178],{"class":68},[54,367,123],{"class":60},[54,369,370],{"class":56,"line":214},[54,371,160],{"class":60},[54,373,374,376],{"class":56,"line":222},[54,375,217],{"class":68},[54,377,108],{"class":60},[54,379,380,382,384,386],{"class":56,"line":234},[54,381,114],{"class":68},[54,383,117],{"class":60},[54,385,229],{"class":68},[54,387,123],{"class":60},[54,389,390],{"class":56,"line":247},[54,391,160],{"class":60},[17,393,394,395,397],{},"Now you can use ",[51,396,295],{}," directly in your HTML wherever you need that shape.",[17,399,400,401,267,403,267,406,409,410,413,414,417],{},"Real-world example — Bootstrap's grid system (",[51,402,295],{},[51,404,405],{},".row",[51,407,408],{},".col",") is \"container separation\". Content like ",[51,411,412],{},"ul>li"," or pagination can sit inside any of those containers — header, footer, wherever. If you write ",[51,415,416],{},".header ul li",", your CSS is locked into the header and can't be reused elsewhere.",[17,419,420],{},"In plain English — \"content should be reusable inside any container; avoid hard-coding content inside a specific container.\"",[12,422,36],{"id":423},"separation-of-structure-from-skin",[17,425,426],{},"The core idea — extract shared base styles, then make visual style a separate, reusable layer.",[17,428,429],{},"Wait, isn't this just SMACSS Module? Pretty close — but OOCSS focuses purely on one thing: if it's visual style, it's its own class. Example:",[44,431,433],{"className":96,"code":432,"language":98,"meta":49,"style":49},".btn {\n  width: 20px;\n  height: 100px;\n  color: red;\n  background-color: red;\n}\n",[51,434,435,442,455,468,478,489],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,436,437,440],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,438,439],{"class":68},".btn",[54,441,108],{"class":60},[54,443,444,446,448,451,453],{"class":56,"line":111},[54,445,129],{"class":68},[54,447,117],{"class":60},[54,449,450],{"class":68},"20",[54,452,138],{"class":137},[54,454,123],{"class":60},[54,456,457,459,461,464,466],{"class":56,"line":126},[54,458,146],{"class":68},[54,460,117],{"class":60},[54,462,463],{"class":68},"100",[54,465,138],{"class":137},[54,467,123],{"class":60},[54,469,470,472,474,476],{"class":56,"line":143},[54,471,114],{"class":68},[54,473,117],{"class":60},[54,475,178],{"class":68},[54,477,123],{"class":60},[54,479,480,483,485,487],{"class":56,"line":157},[54,481,482],{"class":68},"  background-color",[54,484,117],{"class":60},[54,486,178],{"class":68},[54,488,123],{"class":60},[54,490,491],{"class":56,"line":163},[54,492,160],{"class":60},[17,494,495],{},"Extract the visual style:",[44,497,499],{"className":96,"code":498,"language":98,"meta":49,"style":49},".btn-red {\n  color: red;\n  background-color: red;\n}\n\n.btn {\n  width: 20px;\n  height: 100px;\n}\n",[51,500,501,508,518,528,532,536,542,554,566],{